snippet.textDisplay:
I was thinking about this on Wednesday, funnily enough.

This makes sense to me, purely looking at it from a Conor standpoint:

Conor v Nate 3
Usman v Jorge
Khabib v Tony

If Conor wins, he progresses to the winner of Usman v Jorge.

Justin Gaethje gets the winner of Khabib v Tony.

If Conor wins, he gets that winner too. Gets to go for his champ-champ thing again (champ-champ-champ if we include the BMF belt) and then probably rides off into the sunset to go and try for that boxing world title that he wants.

Of course, there are a lot of variables there, he might not even beat Nate, who knows.

Do you risk Conor losing (for the second time) against a guy like Nate, who’s not a world champion, or even a gimmick champion, or a #1 contender, or do you risk a loss to someone like a Khabib/tony/Usman (actual world champions) or at least Jorge is a #1 contender and a gimmick champion PLUS...a legit 170lb (as opposed to Nate and cowboy who were both more like puffed up lightweights)
Flat out fact: the brand of Conor McGregor is hurt way less by a loss to Usman or Jorge or Khabib than it is to Nate. With Usman they can say “well he’s the champion” and even with Jorge they can say “well maybe it turns out Conor shouldn’t be fighting real welterweights after all”
And losing to Khabib again they can say “well Khabib is the GOAT and the champ, so there’s no shame”
But losing twice to Nate Diaz, even at 170 is a huge blemish on Conor’s record.
If I’m his manager or Dana, I don’t take that risk (even if I personally believe that he would win the fight, which I do....but even then I ask myself “what do we gain from this? He already beat him”

You often bring up bow trilogy fights are so big in combat sports but you’ve neglected to mention they are usually world title fights. Having a trilogy fight against a contender when you’ve got a chance to fight a champion in two different weight classes (and I mean world champion btw) doesn’t make any sense. What does Conor gain?
Khabib? Conor gains a world title and the position of lightweight GOAT.
Usman? A third world title and the first person to become champ champ champ
Jorge? A gimmick belt and some serious bragging rights for beating a true #1 contender at a 3rd weight class.
Nate? NOTHING! Just another win over a guy he already beat. Compare that to what he risks and it’s not even close to worth it
